<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Kazakh Judge Dismissed for Bribery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan's Senate decided today
to dismiss Supreme Court Chairman Mikhail Malakhov on alleged
bribery, the Kazakhstan Telegraph Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made following a suggestion by President
Nursultan Nazarbayev on May 24.
</P>
<P>
On February 4, Supreme Court Judge Umegen Ikhsamov accused
Malakhov of taking more than 100,000 U.S. dollars and three sedans
in bribes, saying he had evidence to prove the charge.
</P>
<P>
Malakhov has denied the charge, describing it as slanderous,
but he was suspended by a presidential order on April 9.
</P>
<P>
The State Committee for National Security is investigating the
case, which, if proven, would be the worst corruption scandal in
the country in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
