<HEADLINE> Lee Changho Beats Ma Xiaochun at World Go-chess Best </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Lee Chang-ho of South Korea
defeated Ma Xiaochun of China by 2.5 points Monday at the First
World Go-chess Best tournament.
</P>
<P>
The seven-dan Lee won all two previous games and led the
position of the double round-robin tournamnt, which opened in
Tokyo on April 11 with each elite from South Korea, China and
Japan participating.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Masaki Takemiya had one win and one defeat while
nine-dan Ma got winless in two games.
</P>
<P>
The tournament is holding in the three countries in turn and is
expected to conclude in September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
