<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Chamber of Commerce Encourages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe National Chamber of
Commerce (ZNCC)has embarked on a new initiative to encourage
cross-border investment between Zimbabwe and Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Under the initiative, Zimbabwean firms will be encouraged to
visit the northern Zambian town of Livingstone to scout for
investment and trade opportunities.
</P>
<P>
ZNCC Chief Executive Wonder Maisiri said today, "We visited
Livingstone last month at the invitation of our counterparts. We
discovered that the tourist resort, near the Victoria Falls, has
a potential for economic growth."
</P>
<P>
On June 15, the ZNCC will lead a delegation of Zimbabweans to
examine investment opportunities in Livingstone while a group of
Zambians was expected to visit Zimbabwe on a similar mission
before October.
</P>
<P>
ZNCC intends to make similar arrangements with its
counterparts in Botswana, Malawi, Namibia and South Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
