<HEADLINE> Sichuan, Shanghai Advance to Division A </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, central Sichuan Province, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan
and Shanghai have been promoted to Chinese basketball league
Division A on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The two teams were guaranteed their Division A spots after
winning their Division B semi-finals to enter Tuesday's final.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan edged Jiangsu Nangang 89-88 on a free throw with ten
second left in overtime. The host tied Nangang 76-76 in the
regulation.
</P>
<P>
In the other semi-final, Shanghai rallied from a first-half
seven-point deficit to overcome Hebei 87-72.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai and Sichuan will next season replace Vanguard and
Nanjing Army, two bottom sides in Division A last season, which
ended in April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
