<HEADLINE> Pakistan Railway Starts Ambitious Upgrading Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Railway (PR) has
embarked on an ambitious program of rehabilitation and upgradation
of locomotives, which needs 160 million US dollars, a senior PR
official said today.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen in Karachi, M. Ziaullah, new PR General
Manager, said the implementation of the program will bring greater
efficiency in the passenger and cargo train operations in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Ziaullah pointed out that about 60 percent locomotives had
become over-aged, which seriously affected the punctuality of the
train operations.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the locomotives had become as old as 32 years as
against their normal age of 20 years," he added.
</P>
<P>
Most of the loan for the program is provided by Japan, he
said, adding that some international tenders have also been
floated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
