<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Hold International Book Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 120 publishers and
international organizations have booked stands at the 1996
Zimbabwe International Book Fair, which runs from July 26 to
August 3.
</P>
<P>
The theme for this year's book fair, to be held in Harare, is
"Books and Business" and exhibitors will include publishers'
collectives from the United States and Canada, the Caribbean,
Germany, Norway, Switzerland and the United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the book fair said in a statement the African
Publishers' Network, which represents 22 Anglophone, Francophone
and Lusophone African countries, will have its own pavilion.
</P>
<P>
Other special features of the international exhibits will include
a display of African-American titles from the National Association of
Black Book Publishers of the United States, a collective exhibit of
Swiss publishers with African links and a display from the marketing
unit of Norwegian International Non-fiction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
