<HEADLINE> 40 Armed Robbers Escape From Nigeria's Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Forty condemned armed robbers
escaped from the Bauchi Main Prison in Nigeria at the weekend, an
official report said here today.
</P>
<P>
The News Agency of Nigeria report quoted a prison official as
saying that six notorious armed robbers from outside, led by the
No. 1 armed robber in the country, Jerry Bendal, used a rope to
scale the main walls of the prison at about 3 a.m. on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The six men went straight to the condemned criminals' cell,
broke it open and allowed all the inmates to escape although
Jerry had organized the jail-break to only free two of his boys,
one Charles and another Dauda who had earlier been condemned to
death by a robbery tribunal.
</P>
<P>
According to prison sources, Jerry and his men came to the
prison with sophisticated machine guns, adding that one warder
lost his life during the fracas while five others who sustained
serious injuries were admitted to hospital.
</P>
<P>
They said the warders, who only had batons, were unable to
withstand the onslaught, adding that at the end of the operation,
there were only 11 condemned armed robbers left in the prison.
</P>
<P>
The Abuchi State Deputy Commissioners of Police and the
Assistant Commissioner of Police in charge of the investigation
and intelligence Bureau have since visited the scene and ordered
an investigation.
</P>
<P>
Both officers declined to comment on the incident.
</P>
<P>
Armed robbery has remained rampant despite a war to crack down
on it announced by the military government led by General Sani
Abacha.
</P>
<P>
Last week, armed robbers stormed the Nigerian Railway Police
in the northern Kaduna State and robbered cars and other
properties in the Nacerian National Railway compound in Lagos
where hundreds of Chinese railway experts stayed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
