<HEADLINE> Solely Foreign-owned Excavator Enterprise in Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Daewoo Heavy Industries Yantai
Company, an excavator-building enterprise solely owned by Daewoo
Heavy Industries of the Republic of Korea (ROK), has gone into
production in the east China seaside resort of Yantai.
</P>
<P>
Its first 30 excavators have been exported to ROK and Southeast
Asia.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo Heavy Industries Yantai Company has been built in Yantai
Development Zone at a cost of some 60 million US
dollars. Construction of the plant started in early 1995 and went
into experimental production in March this year.
</P>
<P>
Occupying a land area of 200,000 square meters, the factory has
introduced facilities from ROK, Japan, the United States and
Germany. It is engaged in the production of various types of
excavators up to the world advanced levels of the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
Corporate sources say that the new enterprise will turn out
1,500 excavators this year with an output value of nearly one
billion yuan. The enterprise is expected to produce two billion
yuan in output value next year.  
