<HEADLINE> Shandong to Start Cement Joint Venture with US Cement Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Cement Plant has agreed with
United States cement giant VSC to start a cement joint venture in
Shandong, east China.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement the Shandong Cement Plant will invest 520
million yuan and the US partner will invest 499 million yuan in
the venture, making up 51.04 percent and 48.96 percent of the
shares respectively in the new plant.
</P>
<P>
When the project is completed, the Sino-US joint venture will
be capable of producing 800,000 tons of cement annually, pushing
cement output in the Shandong Cement Plant to a total of 1.6
million tons, which makes the joint venture the largest cement
producer in Shandong. 
</P>
