<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Reiterates Peaceful Unification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice-Premier Qian Qichen
today reiterated that the country's stand and policies on Taiwan
remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
He said the principle of peaceful reunification and the "one
country, two systems" policy will be observed in the long run.
</P>
<P>
Qian, also Minister of Foreign Affairs, made the remarks when
delivering a report to the non-Party members on the current
international situation and on the struggle against "Taiwan
independence".
</P>
<P>
Leaders of National People's Congress Standing Committee,
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, democratic parties, and non-party personages, among
others, heard the report.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that the current international situation is
developing towards relaxation, which in general is favourable to
China's economic development.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has obtained great achievements in the
struggle against "Taiwan Independence" since last June, which is
of strategic importance for relationships across the Taiwan
Straits and the political trend in Taiwan in the long run.
</P>
<P>
"Our struggle against 'Taiwan Independence' has presented our
view clearly to the whole world that the Taiwan question is purely
an internal affair of China," Qian said, adding that it also told
the Taiwan authority and people that 'Taiwan Independence' will
not work.
</P>
<P>
"We will never commit ourselves to abandoning the use of force
on the Taiwan question, " Qian said, adding that it is to ensure
the implementation of the principle of peaceful reunification and
the policy of "one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the "one China" principle should be observed
strictly, noting that the principle is the basis of the
cross-Strait relationships and the milestone of peaceful
reunification.
</P>
<P>
He also told the meeting that the mainland should promote
economic cooperation and other exchanges across the
Straits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
