<HEADLINE> World Champion Gao in Top Form for Atlanta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, Qinghai Province, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese World Cup
walking champion Gao Hongmiao said Tuesday that she is in best
ever form both physically and psychologically, that increases her
confidence for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"Up to now, I have no injury and no psychological pressure on
myself," the Chinese said at Duoba Sports Training Base, some 40
kilometers west of Xining.
</P>
<P>
Gao, 22, who took the gold medal in the 10 kilometers race with
42 minutes 19 seconds at the World Cup walking tournament in
Beijing in April last year, arrived Duoba last weekend for a
plateau training in the leadup to the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"I'm more confident now that I will have good performance at
the Olympics," said Gao, who also took 10 kms at the 1994 Asian
Games in Hiroshima, Japan.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time that Gao has trained in this 2,300-meter
Qinghai Plateau. And she said she felt comfortable and even did
not experience restrained by the high altitude during the training
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chuntang of Gao's coach also confirmed that her training
times were satisfation.
</P>
<P>
Gao ranked No. 11 in the world this year, but Wang said the
ranking could not reflect her actual competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Wang, however, also said Gao, the only Chinese woman who could
walk the 10 kms within 42 minutes, will face strong challenges
from athletes from Russia, Australia and Hungary with comparable
times.
</P>
<P>
The coach said he will focus on improving Gao's tactics,
psychological stableness and stamina in the six-week training here
before they fly for Atalant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
