<HEADLINE> Malaysia To Conquer World's Highest Peak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia on Tuesday expressed
its ambition to conquer Mount Qomolangma, the highest peak in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian prime minister Mahathir Mohamad on Tuesday night
launched a national project aiming at making Malaysia the first
Southeast Asian country to conquer Qomolangma.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, 20 Malaysian mountaineerers will try to
plant the Malaysian flag at the 8,848-meter-high summit in May
next year.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the project is a brainchild of Mahathir,
who once said: "We must have confidence to achieve all of our
dreams. This includes climbing Mountain Qomolangma, sailing across
the Pacific."
</P>
<P>
The project, jointly organized by the Youth and Sports
Ministry, Malaysian Climbing Association and Sport and Culture
Foundation of Malaysia, will cost 4.5 million Malaysian Ringgit
(about 1.8 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that of the 20 climbers selected for the
expedition, only 12 will trek to the top part of the mountain.
</P>
</TEXT>
