<HEADLINE> Prachakorn Thai Party Urged to Stay in Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of six of the seven Thai
coalition government parties met today requesting the Prachakorn
Thai (Thai citizen) Party to stay in the government.
</P>
<P>
The Prachakorn Thai Party made a decision last week to quit the
government later this month.
</P>
<P>
The party was not happy with Prime Minister Banharn
Silpa-Archa's May 28 cabinet reshuffle, in which the Palang Dharma
(virtue force) Party, whose five cabinet members resigned on May
24, returned to the government, and the Nam Thai (Thai leadership)
party was given an additional cabinet post.
</P>
<P>
Prachakorn Thai has the same number of parliamentary seats as
Nam Thai.
</P>
<P>
It is feared that Prachakorn Thai's threatened withdrawal could
rock the government.
</P>
<P>
Opposition parties claim that the prime minister has lost
control of the situation and should resign to make way for a new
government.
</P>
<P>
The coalition government consists of the Chart Thai (Thai
nation), New Aspiration, Palang Dharma (virtue force), Social
Action, Prachakorn Thai (Thai citizen), Nam Thai (Thai leadership)
and Muan Chon (the masses) parties, which together have 232 of the
total 391 parliamentary seats.
</P>
<P>
Prachakorn Thai has 18 seats.  
</P>
