<HEADLINE> Ariane-5 Destructed After Lift-off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A new generation Ariane-5 rocket was
destructed by ground controllers about 40 seconds after lifting
off today from Kourou in French Guiana, French television said.
</P>
<P>
The 8.4 billion dollar rocket was destructed because it veered
off course, a space official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Four identical scientific satellites with the rocket were also
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Television pictures showed the rocket suddenly went off its
course and exploded with debris falling from the sky.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the control center said the failure of the launch
is not immediately known and is being investigated.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rocket blasted off at 1233 GMT from the European
Space Agency launch center in Kourou.
</P>
<P>
The launch of the Ariane-5 had been delayed about 50 minutes
due to bad weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
