<HEADLINE> Hunan's Development Zones Attractive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The five high-tech industrial
development zones in Central China's Hunan province are becoming
magnets for business enterprises, thanks to better infrastructure
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The zones covering 97.5 square kilometers are home to 575
high-tech enterprises, which obtained a total income of 4.95
billion yuan last year, up 168.4 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
They generated industrial output totalling four billion yuan
and profits and taxes amounting to 737 million yuan, up 128
percent and 153 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Products such as central air-conditioners, super-hard materials
and personal computers produced at the zone compete well on the
domestic market.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that the zones have made full use of
their advantages in technology to help old enterprises transform
their technologies and equipment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year the five zones had attracted 120
foreign-funded enterprises, and imported foreign investment of
more than 200 million US dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
