<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Amir Meets with Chinese Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh Jaber
Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah met with visiting Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian today, expressing hope that the friendly relations and
cooperation between the two countries would be further developed
and consolidated.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti leader expressed his gratitude to the Chinese
people and government for the support to the Kuwaiti people in
their just struggle of maintaining integrity and sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that China would continue to support the
Kuwaiti people in solving the remaining problems of the Gulf War,
especially in securing the comeback of the 600 prisoners of war,
who Kuwait has insistently claimed are still under the detention
of the Iraq regime.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Chi, also vice-chairman of the Chinese Central
Military Commission, said that the Chinese government attaches
importance to developing friendly cooperative relations between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Following his visit to Saudi Arabia, Chi arrived here Monday
leading a 15-member military delegation for a four-day visit to
Kuwait, the second leg of his Middle East tour which will also
take him to the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Chi also held talks with his Kuwaiti counterpart Ahmed
al-Humoud al-Sabah today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese defense minister will leave Kuwait Thursday for the
UAE to continue his Middle East tour ever made by a Chinese
defense minister to the region.  
</P>
