<HEADLINE> Collective Contract System for Foreign-funded Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China plans to implement a
collective contract system in all foreign-funded enterprises in
three years.
</P>
<P>
It will provide a clear description of pay, work time,
vacation and other matters to protect the rights and interests of
workers.
</P>
<P>
According to a symposium which closed in Tianjin today, 30
percent of the 40,000 plus foreign-funded firms in China are
expected to practise collective consultation and contract systems
this year.
</P>
<P>
An official from All-China Federation of Trade Unions said, up
to 2,300 foreign-funded firms have already signed collective
contracts, with Jiangsu, Shandong, Shanghai and Zhejiang leading
the rest of China.
</P>
<P>
Collective contracts and consultation is a common system in
many countries in solving labor disputes, he said, adding it is a
general norm between employers and employees in labor relations.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
