<HEADLINE> BOC Becomes China's Second Largest Credit Card Issuer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China, which issued
China's first credit card ten years ago, has issued 3.5 million
Great Wall cards, a bank official said.
</P>
<P>
To date the savings balance of the Great Cards stands at 19.3
billion yuan (about $2.3 billion) and annual transaction volumes
reaches 300 billion yuan (about $36 billion).
</P>
<P>
With an annual increase of 134 percent, BOC has become the
country's second largest credit card issuer.
</P>
<P>
The bank official said BOC has signed an agreement with seven
giant international credit card firms at act as their acquiring
agent, including Federal Card, MasterCard, Visa, American Express,
and Dinners Club.
</P>
<P>
China now has about 10 million credit card holders. The
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China ranks first among China's
credit card issuers with five million cards issued. 
</P>
</TEXT>
