<DOCNO> XIE19960604.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swiss Government Slaps Arms Ban on Sri Lankan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Swiss Authorities have banned Sri
Lankan expatriates there from buying or carrying weapons following
a series of violent incidents involving extortion of funds for
Tamil rebels, a local evening newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The measure, which will come into force today, is aimed at
curbing feuding within the Sri Lankan Tamil community in
Switzerland, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Swiss police in April this year arrested 15 members of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), including the group's
leader N. Muralidaran, according to local press reports early.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that the LTTE rebels have been frequently
accused of extorting money from Tamils living in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Some 20,000 of Sri Lanka Tamil people are now living in
Switzerland as refugees since 1983 when the LTTE rebels launched
a guerrilla war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
