<HEADLINE> Rising Balloon Raises Human Environment Awareness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The ultimate giant panda is on a
trip around the world to rally human support for environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
The panda, actually a 27-meter-high panda-shaped hot-air
balloon, has left Chengdu, capital city of southwest China's
Sichuan Province for Shenzhen in south China.
</P>
<P>
Its destinations also include the Chinese cities of Guilin,
Xichang, Kunming, Urumqi and Beijing, as well as Japan, the United
States and Australia.
</P>
<P>
A publicity campaign, "Friends of Giant Panda" will be held as
the balloon arrives at each place, according to the activity
organizers, the China Association of Wild Animal Protection and a
Japanese foundation.
</P>
<P>
They said they chose the giant panda, one of the most
endangered animals on earth, as a symbol of the activity in
order to raise public concern for environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Various events have been held to mark the launch of the balloon
in Chengdu, including petition signing, a picture show and
artistic performances. 
</P>
