<HEADLINE> Ten-Year Government Bonds To Be Issued </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Finance is to
issue 12 billion yuan ten-year government bonds, the longest term
since the ministry resumed bond issues in the early 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, the seventh batch issued this year, will be issued
from June 14 to July 11, and can be traded when the issue is
completed, according to the Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry does not mention the interest rate on the bonds
but says that it will pay the interest rate on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will be first underwritten by primary dealers through
bidding, a news release notes.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance has issued abut 100 billion yuan worth
of treasury bonds so far this year. 
