<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All People in Guangdong to Be Relieved out of Poverty Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Economic boom province of
Guangdong in south China is striving to help all its
mountain-living people out of poverty by the end of next year.
</P>
<P>
During the period the provincial government will spend 500
million yuan (about 60 million US dollars) in the mountainous
areas in the province's northern part for poverty relief programs.
</P>
<P>
The provincial financial department will arrange low-interest
loans to help poor areas develop agricultural and energy
exploitation projects.
</P>
<P>
The department will also set aside 20 million yuan of subsidies
to remove impoverished people out of limestone areas.
</P>
<P>
Eight of the booming coastal cities in Guangdong have been
asked to undertake responsibility for aiding poor people in 16
mountainous counties.
</P>
<P>
Mountainous areas account for 65 percent of the province's
total territory. Over the past decade, the average per capita
income of mountainous farmers has been raised from 410 yuan to
2,200 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The number of poor people in the province has been cut to
800,000 from four million ten years ago.
</P>
<P>
Across the country the central government is working out plans
to make all people in China bid farewell to poverty by the end of
the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
