<HEADLINE> Ariane-5 Explodes Soon After Liftoff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A new generation Ariane-5 rocket
exploded about 40 seconds after lifting off today from Kourou in
French Guiana, French television showed.
</P>
<P>
Four identical scientific satellites with the rocket were also
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Television pictures showed the rocket suddenly veering off
course and exploding with debris falling from the sky.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the control center said the reason for the
explosion is not immediately known and is being investigated.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rocket blasted off at 1233 GMT from the European
Space Agency launch center in Kourou.
</P>
<P>
The failure of the maiden flight of the Ariane rocket is a
serious setback to Western Europe's space industry, which is
struggling to maintain its lead in the competitive commercial
satellite launch market, observers noted.
</P>
<P>
The launch of the Ariane-5 had been delayed about 50 minutes
due to bad weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
