<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Death Rate of Stomach Cancer High in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Statistics show that about 160,000
Chinese people die from stomach cancer each year.
</P>
<P>
According to a new medical book, over 90 percent of patients
who suffer from stomach cancer can survive its early stages if the
stomach is removed promptly.
</P>
<P>
But in most cases, the stomach cancer has developed to an
advanced stage when diagnosed, and the patients cannot be fully
cured through surgery.
</P>
<P>
Two-thirds of stomach cancer patients depend on chemotherapy to
ease pain and prolong their lives. Radiation treatment has
developed rapidly during recent years because of advances in
medical science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Chemotherapy is expected to play a more important role in
cancer treatment, said Li Jingtai, director of the General
Hospital of the PLA Air Force.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
