<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3,400-Year-Old Gingko Tree "Coughs" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Every night in a temple in Luxian
county, a 3,400-year-old gingko tree produced the sound of coughs
like an old man.
</P>
<P>
This is the first such case ever reported in the country. And
so far experts have no explanations for the strange occurrence in
east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The tree, which is regarded locally as a living fossil, is 24.7
meters high and 15.7 meters in circumference. It has attracted
hundreds of visitors each night since the news was made public,
according to the "Beijing Evening News."
</P>
<P>
Monks at the temple said the tree is quiet during the day, but
"coughs" lightly several times at night.  
</P>
</TEXT>
