<HEADLINE> Chinese Folk Artist Crafts Jade Instruments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese folk artist in northwest
China's Shaanxi Province has crafted two musical instruments made
of jade.
</P>
<P>
The instruments are a violin and an erhu, a two-stringed
bowed Chinese traditional musical instrument.
</P>
<P>
Gu Yangfeng, 48 years old, said that he cut and polished over
30 pieces of precious jade stones for his musical works of art.
</P>
<P>
"I started the crafting work four months ago," he said, adding
that the instruments are 4.8-kilograms in weight and black in color.
</P>
<P>
Many musicians who have played the instruments praised the
deliberate and beautiful acoustic qualities.
</P>
<P>
The musical instruments will be displayed at the 30th World
Geology Conference which opens in Beijing later this year.
