<HEADLINE> Beijing Tightens Reins on Elevators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital will issue work
permits to the manufacturers of the city's elevators in an attempt
to better control the management and repair of the city's lifts.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time the country has required municipal
governments to issue permits, rather than the manufacturer's
themselves.
</P>
<P>
Under government regulations, elevator passengers are required
to witness the signing of the permit by elevator manufacturers,
repairmen and quality control specialists, according to a recent
local conference on elevators.
</P>
<P>
As of July 1, only repair firms authorized by the elevator
manufacturers will be permitted to make repairs. Unauthorized
firms that attempt to work on elevators will be severely punished.
</P>
<P>
So far, 105 repair companies have applied to handle the city's
lift repairs.
</P>
<P>
At present, eight domestic and joint-venture elevator
manufacturers have been authorized to sell their elevators in
Beijing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
