<HEADLINE> Shanghai Has 1,523 Skyscrapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's largest city has the
tallest buildings in the country, with a total of 1,523
skyscrapers that cover an area of 20.65 million square meters.
</P>
<P>
Highest of all is the Shanghai Commercial Mansion, which stands
at 165 meters and boasts 48 floors. It totals an area of 185,000
square meters.
</P>
<P>
According to the local "City Herald," 1,423 out of the 1,523
skyscrapers, with an area of 19.54 million square meters, were
built after 1949. In 1995 alone, the city constructed 219
skyscrapers, covering an area of 3.78 million square meters.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-three of the buildings have more than 30 floors, 411 have
20 to 29 floors.
</P>
<P>
The skyscrapers include 1,036 residential buildings, 215 office
buildings, 56 hotels, 54 workshops, 42 inns, 28 hospitals, 18
schools and eight storehouses. 
</P>
