<HEADLINE> Macao Internet Subscribers Total 1,600 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MACAO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The number of customers of the
Internet Service in Macao has totaled 1,600 one year after the
introduction of the service in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Macao Telecommunications Company (CTM) said
that about 70 percent of the users are individuals and the remaining
subscribers are companies or government organs.
</P>
<P>
Four government departments of Macao, including the tourism
department, the statistics department and the Macao City Government
have entered the Internet service.
</P>
<P>
The CTM expects that the number of subscribers will reach
between 2,000 and 2,500 by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Macao Internet service now offers such items as academic
knowledge, news and information, transportation, tourism and trade,
banking and financing, as well as entertainment.
</P>
<P>
A local computer organization has urged the government to take
efficient use of the Internet service to promote Macao, saying
that will be a help to the development of Macao's economy.
</P>
