<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 105-Year-Old Man Dies in Sleep </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- A 105-year-old man died peacefully
in his sleep in early May in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
On the night of April 30, Zhao Zhi'an, who was born in 1891,
ate a dinner of pork and rice at his home in Jingjing county, then
told his family he wanted to sleep, according to the "Beijing
Youth Daily."
</P>
<P>
Early the next morning, when the family tried to wake him, Zhao
said, "I want to continue my sleep. Go mind your own
business. Don't bother me."
</P>
<P>
He soon fell into a coma that lasted four days and
nights. Family members said he even snored. He died on May 4.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said Zhao's body functions were normal, but he died
four days later.
</P>
<P>
Zhao's 81-year-old son said his father was healthy and seldom
ill. The old man liked flowers, taking walks, chatting and reading
books. He was an early riser, exercised regularly, and had a
healthy appetite that favored fish, pork and fruits.
</P>
<P>
As a child, Zhao delivered newspapers in Tianjin. He married in
1909.
</P>
<P>
According to Chinese custom, an old man who dies without pain
dies with happiness.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
