counterpart Amr Moussa arrived at Riyadh on a surprise visit to
Saudi Arabia several hours after a secret talk between Syrian
President Hafez al-Assad and Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak was
held Monday in Cairo, Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian and Egyptian foreign ministers were reportedly to
hold talks with Saudi Foreign Minister Prince Saud Al-Faisal
Al-Saud Monday night on coordinating policies toward the
post-election Israel and organizing an Arab summit to align their
strategies.
</P>
<P>
The sources said if the idea is approved, other Arab parties
directly involved in the Middle East peace process, including
Jordan, Lebanon and the Palestinian National Authority, could be
invited to join the summit..
</P>
<P>
Details of the talks were not available.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that President Hosni Mubarak and his Syrian
counterpart Hafez al-Assad discussed ways of restoring solidarity
among the Arabs before sending their foreign ministers to Riyadh
Monday. 
