<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> TV Shopping Network to Be Launched on AsiaSat 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong-based Asia Satellite
Telecommunications Co. Ltd. (AsiaSat) and the Value Network
(Australasia) Ltd. (TVN) have announced the signing of a lease
agreement for a 36 MHz C-band transponder on AsiaSat 2.
</P>
<P>
The service named as the TV Shopping Network (TVSN) will be
dedicated to the provision of 24-hour TV home shopping throughout
Asia.
</P>
<P>
AsiaSat 2 is the second satellite of AsiaSat which was
successfully launched on November 28, 1995 and began its
commercial operation in January this year.
</P>
<P>
Peter Jackson, Chief Executive Officer of AsiaSat, said that
the agreement will bring one of the first home shopping channels
into Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Reaching over 3.3 billion people in the region, AsiaSat 2 is
certainly the ideal platform to achieve economy of scale for TV
home shopping business," he said.
</P>
<P>
William Schereck, president of TVN, said that TVSN provides the
viewers with the convenience of shopping at home combined with a
broad range of products and services priced to represent good
value.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is only these recent years that TV home
shopping business has been introduced in places outside the United
States. "Given Asia has the world's largest population, and the
fastest-developing economies, its potential for growth is
enormous," he added.
</P>
<P>
TVSN began broadcasting as Australia's first and the only home
shopping channel in December 1995. Home shopping programs are
produced by TVSN and broadcast directly viewers via satellite and
cable TV seven days a week for 24 hours per day.
</P>
<P>
Services will be expanded to the whole of the Asian region when
TVSN commences broadcast on AsiaSat 2 in July this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
