<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Precision machinery maker
Canon Inc. is likely to post about 52 billion yen in its
unconsolidated pretax profit for the first half of the current
business year, registering a 75 percent rise from a year earlier,
a business daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kyodo News Service quoted the Nihon Keizai Shimbun as saying
that Canon's sales of laser beam printers and bubble-jet printers
during the six months to June 30 will each show about a 25 percent
increase from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
