<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 09:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia, Kuwait Support Bahrain in Foiling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia and Kuwait have
expressed their backing for Bahrain in foiling an anti-government
plot which is reportedly backed by Iran.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Saudi western port city of Jeddah today said Saudi
Information Minister Fuad Bin Abdel-Salam bin Mohammed Faresi
declared Monday night that "Saudi Arabia stands by Bahrain in
whatever ensures its security and safeguards its stability and
territorial integrity."
</P>
<P>
Kuwait Crown Prince and Prime Minister Saad al-Abdullah
al-Sabah Monday night also affirmed Kuwait's support and full
solidarity with Bahrain over a telephone call to his Bahrain
counterpart Sheikh Khalifa Bin Sulman Al-Khalifa, official sources
here said today.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain said Monday that it thwarted an attempt by
Iranian-supported armed revolters to topple the Bahrain government.
</P>
<P>
An Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman denied Monday Bahrain's
allegations that Iran was involved in the plot, saying they were
"totally baseless."
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, Kuwait and Bahrain are members of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC), which also groups the United Arab
Emirates, Qatar and Oman. The six countries have close
cooperation ties on various fronts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
