<HEADLINE> Tanmzanian Soldiers Go Rampant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Troops have rampaged in
northern Tanzania Mererani Village, looting and setting ablaze
homes in revenge for the stabbing of a soldier, local reports
said today.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of soldiers invaded Mererani Village, 26 km west of
the northern town of Arusha, on Saturday night and looted and set
ablaze some 15 homes, bars, shops, restaurants and lodging
houses, according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
The raid was in revenge for the stabbing of a soldier in the
village last Wednesday by an unidentified man.
</P>
<P>
The witnesses said the buildings set ablaze burned down as
groups of soldiers guarded them, stopping anyone approaching.
</P>
<P>
"I neither dreamed nor expected that such an inhumane act
would ever happen in such a peaceful country," said Prime
Minister Frederick Sumaye when he visited the village on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister pledged the culprits would be severely
punished and the government would do everything possible to give
food and shelter to the homeless.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the villagers for calm and not to launch any
revenge attacks on soldiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
