<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 24 Singaporeans Get AIDS Virus in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Singapore reported today that in
the first quarter of this year, 24 Singaporeans have been infected
with the Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV), the AIDS virus.
</P>
<P>
Among the 24 infected, 12 have full blown AIDS (Acquired
Immunity Deficiency Syndrome), while the other 12 are virus
carriers.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry said that this has brought the total number
of Singaporeans with HIV to about 440 since 1985.
</P>
<P>
It said that most of the infected caught the disease through
sex and, for this year, more than 20 cases were infected this way,
while three were infected via intravenous drug use.
</P>
<P>
As in earlier years, men formed the majority of the cases,
almost 90 percent. Giving a profile of the victims, the ministry
said most were between 30 and 39 years of age and single.
</P>
<P>
Others were married, divorced or widowed. None of the spouses
of those married have so far been diagnosed with AIDS, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry stressed that the only way to avoid AIDS
was to avoid casual sex and sex with prostitutes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
