<HEADLINE> Japan to Take Specific Measures for 'Jusen' Burden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese Government will take
specific measures to seek additional contributions from financial
institutions for a scheme to liquidate failed "Jusen" housing loan
companies, according to a Kyodo News Service report today.
</P>
<P>
"As far as my responsibility is concerned, no specific measures
have been considered selectively or adopted," Finance Minister
Wataru Kubo said at a news conference.
</P>
