<HEADLINE> Singapore Proposes Dialogue for ASEM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok
Tong has proposed a political and business dialogue mechanism for
the Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM), local television reported today.
</P>
<P>
The proposed dialogue mechanism will be similar to the existing
mechanism within Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) members
whose inputs from the business sector as well as academics and
government officials are combined, the television report said.
</P>
<P>
It said the idea was put forward by Goh when he met Finnish
trade and industry representatives. Goh is now in Helsinki on an
official visit to Finland.
</P>
<P>
ASEM was one of the main topics at talks between Goh and
Finland's Foreign Minister Tarja Halonen on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Goh also proposed ways to build up educational contacts on the
basis of the ASEM contacts during his meeting with his Finnish
counterpart Paavo Lipponen on Monday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
He suggested a scientific and cultural exchange program, which
he said could benefit the scientific and research communities of
both countries.
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers also discussed the setting up of a
dialogue between the governments and business sectors of Asia and
Europe in the context of ASEM, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
