<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Research-oriented Companies Flourishing in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- This capital city of south
China's Guangdong Province has built 2,000 research-oriented
manufacturing companies since it began to implement the policy of
invigorating the economy through science and technology in 1993.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Guangzhou City Science and Technology
Commission said that 158 of the 2,000 manufacturers have been
designated as high-tech companies by the State Science and
Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
The official said that over the past three years, the Guangzhou
City government has concentrated on building the Guangzhou Economic
and Technological Development Zone, the Tianhe High-Tech
Industrial Development Zone, the Nansha Economic and Technological
Development Zone, the Guangzhou Electronics Industrial Park and
the Guangzhou Science and Technology Park.
</P>
<P>
Technological progress now contributes 40 percent to
Guangzhou's economic growth, he said.
</P>
<P>
The per capita gross domestic product (the value of goods and
services produced) in Guangzhou was 19,000 yuan in 1995, meeting
the quota for the year 2000 five years ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, the city government has proclaimed a series of
regulations designed to accelerate economic growth through
scientific and technological progress, aid the development of
high-tech industries, and strengthen management of
non-state-owned, research-oriented companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
