<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Foreign Countries to Attend Shanghai Television Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Several foreign television
stations from 12 countries will participate in the 6th Shanghai
Television Festival this November, sources from the festival's
preparatory committee said today.
</P>
<P>
German television's channel 2, channels 2 and 3 from France,
Japan's NHK, Warner Bros. and the National Broadcasting Company
from the U.S., the British Broadcasting Company and other foreign
national television stations have agreed to attend the upcoming
festival, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The festival will run from November 9-14. Started in 1986, the
cultural event takes place every other year.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the six "White Yulan Magnolia" Awards, the 6th
festival will present awards for best supporting actor and actress.
</P>
<P>
The nominating committee consists of 10 film and television
experts from China, China's Taiwan province, Germany, France,
Japan, the United States, Russia and Canada, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Also held during the festival will be a trade fair on
international television programs, an international exhibition on
broadcasting facilities and a symposium on international
television programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
