<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Launches Overall Agricultural Development Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region
is implementing an agricultural development project that has
produced high yields.
</P>
<P>
The project includes construction of several production bases
of grain, cotton, beets and fruit, which all should be completed
by the end of the century, a regional official said.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang will introduce agro-techniques that are expected to
increase grain output by 1,500 kilograms per hectare, and should
transform low-yield cotton fields so that they produce an output
of at least 1,500 kilograms per hectare.
</P>
<P>
Other expansions include building more livestock farms,
developing water-saving agro-techniques, and expanding the
production of grapes, beets and pears.
</P>
<P>
With vast land resources, an ideal climate and abundant
sunshine, Xinjiang has good prospects for agricultural
development, the officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
