<DOCNO> XIE19960604.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan to China's Railway Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
approved today a 100 million US dollars loan and a 400,000 US
dollars technical assistance grant for the Daxian-Wanxian railway
project in China's Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
The 156 km single-track railway will provide a more efficient
mode of transport and will open a new rail-waterway transportation
route from Sichuan province to the Yangtze River Delta.
</P>
<P>
The project area is situated in one of the 18 poorest regions
in China where the average income is less than one-third of the
national average.
</P>
<P>
The technical assistance grant will assist in the institutional
development of local railways in Sichuan province to operate
successfully in a commercial environment.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed in June 2000.
</P>
</TEXT>
