<HEADLINE> Environmental Protection in China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Following is the full text of the
white paper entitled "Environmental Protection in China" issued by
the Information Office of the State Council here today:
</P>
<P>
Foreword
</P>
<P>
China is a developing country and now it is confronted with the
dual task of developing the economy and protecting the
environment. Proceeding from its national conditions, China has,
in the process of promoting its overall modernization program,
made environmental protection one of its basic national policies,
regarded the realization of sustainable development as an
important strategy and carried out throughout the country
large-scale pollution prevention and control as well as ecological
environment protection. Over the 18 years since the start of
reform and opening up to the outside world, China's gross national
product (GNP) has achieved a sustained annual growth of around 10
percent, while its environmental quality has basically steered
clear of the outcome of corresponding deterioration. Practice has
proved that the principle China has adopted to achieve
coordinated development between the economy, the society and the
environment has been effective.
</P>
<P>
As a member of the international community, China, while making
great efforts to protect its own environment, has taken an active
part in international environmental affairs, striven to promote
international cooperation in the field of environmental
protection, and earnestly fulfilled its international
obligations. All these have fully shown the sincerity and
determination of the Chinese government and people to protect the
global environment.
</P>
<P>
What efforts has China made to protect its own environment?
What is the situation of environmental protection in China? On the
occasion of the annual World Environment Day, which falls on June
5, here is an account.
</P>
<P>
Contents
</P>
<P>
Foreword
</P>
<P>
I.  The Choice of Implementing a Sustainable Development Strategy
</P>
<P>
II. Improving the Legal and Administrative Systems Step by Step
</P>
<P>
III. The Prevention and Control of Industrial Pollution and the
</P>
<P>
Comprehensive Improvement of the Urban Environment
</P>
<P>
IV. National Land Improvement and Rural Environmental Protection
</P>
<P>
V.  Protection of the Ecological Environment and Biodiversity
</P>
<P>
VI. Environmental Science and Technology, and Environmental
</P>
<P>
Publicity and Education
</P>
<P>
VII. Taking Vigorous Action to Promote International
</P>
<P>
Cooperation
</P>
<P>
Concluding Remarks
</P>
</TEXT>
