<HEADLINE> Foreign Tourists Robbed in Kenya's National Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Armed bandits on Monday attacked a
tourists convoy of seven mini-buses at the Tsavo West National
Park and robbed them of money and personal effects, the local
"Daily Nation" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place two kilometres from Chyulu Hill, where
German tourists were robbed of 10,000 Kenya Shillings, 30
Deutsche Marks and a wristwatch.
</P>
<P>
The German tourists were rescued by the Kenyan Police of
General Service Unit (GSU).
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred two days after Kenyan President Daniel
arap Moi said that his government will restructure security
forces to cub the insecurity in the country so as to attract
foreign and local investments.
</P>
<P>
The president was reacting to the recent two incidents in
which one U.N driver and a British aid worker were killed by
thugs separetely in Nairobi and in Nyeri District. 
</P>
