<HEADLINE> China, Jamaica to Expand Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi said today that the Chinese
government encourages Chinese entrepreneurs to invest in Jamaica
and conduct all kinds of economic and trade cooperations there.
</P>
<P>
She made the remark in Beijing in a meeting today with Seymour
Mullings, Jamaica's deputy prime minister and minister of foreign
affairs and foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers exchanged views on the expansion of
bilateral economic and trade collaboration during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Mullings expressed his thanks for China's support to Jamaica
and told Wu that Jamaica welcomes Chinese entrepreneurs to invest
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Mullings is here on a visit to China as guest of his Chinese
counterpart Qian Qichen. 
