<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 25 Zimbabwean Farms Acquired for Resettlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government has
acquired 25 farms during the last six months and is in the
process of acquiring 23 others for resettlement.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Lands and Water Development Kumbirai Kangai said
here yesterday the government acknowledged the land hunger
problem in the country, but would continue its efforts to acquire
land for resettlement as long as funds permit.
</P>
<P>
He criticized those illegally settling on designated land.
although the government was aware of the land problem, it would
not tolerate people settling themselves haphazardly on state
land.
</P>
<P>
More than 6,000 squatters have moved onto state land and the
result has been quite adverse with the wanton destruction of the
environment, diseases and crime becoming the order of the day at
such settlements.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the resettlement programme needs to be done
in an orderly fashion and that the people need to be assessed to
determine their potential to succeed in agriculture before land
is allocated to them.
</P>
<P>
So far 60,000 families have been resettled while nearly 80,000 are
still waiting to be allocated land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
