<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues White Paper on Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The Information Office of the State
Council here today issued a white paper entitled "Environmental
Protection in China."
</P>
<P>
In the 20,000-word white paper, the office gave a detailed
account on the country's choice of implementing a sustainable
development strategy, improving the legal and administrative systems
on environmental protection step by step, the prevention and
control of industrial pollution and comprehensive improvement of
the urban environment, national land improvement and rural environmental
protection, protection of the ecological environment and
biodiversity, environmental science and technology and
enironmental publicity and education, and promoting international
cooperation in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The office said that China is a developing country and is
confronted with the dual task of developing the economy and
protecting the environment. Proceeding from its national
conditions, China has, in the process of promoting its overall
modernization program, made environmental protection one of its
basic national policies, regarded the realization of sustainable
development as an important strategy and carried out throughout
the country large-scale pollution prevention and control as well
as ecological environment protection.
</P>
<P>
Over the 18 years since the start of reform and opening up to
the outside world, China's gross national product (GNP) has
achieved a sustained annual growth of around 10 percent, while its
environmental quality has basically steered clear of the outcome
of corresponding deterioration. Practice has proved that the
principle China has adopted to achieve coordinated development
between the economy, the society and the environment has been
effective, the office said.
</P>
<P>
As a member of the international community, China, while making
great efforts to protect its own environment, has taken an active
part in international environmental affairs, striven to promote
international cooperation in the field of environmental
protection, and earnestly fulfilled its international
obligations. All these have fully shown the sincerity and
determination of the Chinese government and people to protect the
global environment, the office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
