<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> White Paper: China Prevents deterioration of Environment (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China said in a white paper today
that its environment has basically steered clear of deterioration
with the fact that its gross national product (GNP) has been
growing by around 10 percent annually over the past 18 years of
reforms and opening up.
</P>
<P>
The white paper on Environmental Protection in China, issued
here today by the Information Office of the State Council, said
that the principle China has adopted to achieve coordinated
economic, social and environmental development has been proved to
be effective.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has paid great attention to
environmental issues arising from the country's population growth
and economic development, and has made environmental protection an
important aspect of the improvement of the people's living
standards and quality of life, the some 20,000-word white paper
said.
</P>
<P>
In order to promote coordinated development between the
economy, the society and the environment, China enacted and
implemented a series of principles, policies, laws and measures
for environmental protection in the 1980s, it said.
</P>
<P>
"The Environmental Protection Law of the People's Republic of
China" is the cardinal law for environmental protection in China,
the white paper said. The law has established the basic principle
for coordinated development between economic construction, social
progress and environmental protection, and defined the rights and
duties of governments at all levels, all units and individuals as
regards environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
China has enacted and promulgated many special laws on
environmental protection as well as laws on natural resources
related to environmental protection, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960604.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> White Paper: China Prevents deterioration of Environment (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese government has also enacted more than 30
administrative decrees regarding environmental protection. In
addition, departments concerned have also issued a number of
administrative rules and decrees on environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
To implement the state environmental protection laws and
regulations, local people's congresses and people's governments,
proceeding from specific conditions in their own respective areas,
have enacted and promulgated more than 600 local laws on
environmental protection, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995, China had promulgated state environmental
standards on 364 items. As stipulated in Chinese law, the
environmental quality standards and pollutant discharge standards
are compulsory standards, and those who violate these compulsory
environmental standards must bear the corresponding legal
responsibility, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
The white paper said that the Chinese government regards
prevention and control of industrial pollution as the focal point
of environmental protection. Thanks to the unremitting efforts
over the past 20-odd years, China has made great progress in this
regard.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960604.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> White Paper: China Prevents deterioration of Environment (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1995 the waste water treatment rate of the industrial
enterprises at and above the county level in China reached 76.8
percent; the smoke and dust removal rate of waste gas from burning
fuel, 88.2 percent; waste gas purification rate from production
processes, 68.9 percent; and the comprehensive utilization rate of
industrial solid waste, 43 percent, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
Output value attained through the comprehensive utilization of
the industrial "three wastes" came to 19 billion yuan, it added.
</P>
<P>
China is a country with coal as its main energy source. Seventy
percent of the smoke and dust in the air and 90 percent of the
sulfur dioxide emission come from burning coal, the white paper
said.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the white paper continued, the cities with
concentrated industries and their population suffer from serious
air pollution. Acid rain has occurred, and the situation has gone
from bad to worse in some regions and cities.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has adopted measures such as developing
clean coal technology and clean burning technology, and collecting
sulfur dioxide emission fees, to control acid rain, the white
paper said.
</P>
<P>
A long-term study by Chinese experts on the issue of acid rain
proves that the precursors of acid rain generated from the
emission source in China's inland areas are mainly spread within
Chinese territory, mainly in the areas south of the Yangtze River
and in regions east of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, and in the
Sichuan Basin, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
At present, 68.4 percent of urban residents in China use gas
for fuel and heating; the centralized disposal rate of urban
sewage is 20 percent; the innocuity rate of urban garbage and
fecal disposal is 45.4 percent; and the afforestation rate is 23.8
percent, the white paper said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960604.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> White Paper: China Prevents deterioration of Environment (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National land improvement is part of China's work in
implementing the sustainable development strategy. Since the start
of the reform and opening up to the outside world, the Chinese
government has carried out national land improvement on a large
scale, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
Notable successes have been attained in harnessing major
rivers and lakes. Since the foundation of New China in 1949, the
Chinese government has taken comprehensive measures to develop and
harness the major rivers and lakes, with emphasis on the
prevention and control of flood and water-logging, as an important
task of the construction of water conservation facilities.
</P>
<P>
During the Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995), the main
dikes were heightened and reinforced, waterways were cleaned up,
and flood diversion projects were built on the middle and lower
reaches of the Yangtze River, the lower reaches of the Yellow
River, and other major rivers and lakes, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
The construction of a group of key projects for water control
and other uses were completed or started. To compensate for lack
of water resources in northern areas, the Chinese government
vigorously promoted the planning and construction of
water-diversion projects between different drainage basins, it
added.
</P>
<P>
In November 1995, it sponsored an overall feasibility study of
the middle, eastern and western lines projects for diverting water
from south to north.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Project is a gigantic, trans-century project
for harnessing and developing the Yangtze River. When it is
completed, floods on the upper reaches will be effectively
controlled and areas on the middle and lower reaches of the river
will be able to improve their anti-flood capability, thus
lessening the harmful effects on the ecological
environment. Hydroelectricity, which will be the energy discharged
by the project, causes much less pollution than coal-burning power
plants, the white paper said, adding that the Chinese government
will adopt a sequence of measures to minimize the unfavorable
effects on the ecology and the environment that could be caused by
the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
China has traditionally been an agricultural country. In
developing agricultural production, the Chinese government
attaches great importance to rural environmental protection, and
has taken the development of eco-agriculture as an important means
to realize the coordinated development of the environment and the
economy, the white paper said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960604.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> White Paper: China Prevents deterioration of Environment (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At present, the 50 counties designated by the state for
eco-agricultural experiment are playing a good and exemplary role
in the country, spurring development of eco-agriculture in 10
prefectures and over 100 counties, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, the total grain output in the
experimental counties has increased by 15 percent, output per mu
by more than 10 percent, and the income per capita is 12 percent
higher than the average level of the surrounding areas, the white
paper said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, work has started in an all-round way to
construct some 100 ecological demonstration areas, mainly at the
county level, in order to promote regional sustainable
development, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government regards ecological environmental
protection as the focal point of its environmental protection
work. Through protracted efforts, China has made great
achievements in the protection and construction of the ecological
environment, the white paper said.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1950s, the Chinese government has organized
large-scale tree planting activities and stepped up efforts for
the fostering, protection and management of forest resources and
consequently has made great progress in rational utilization of
forest resources.
</P>
</TEXT>
