<HEADLINE> Cambodia Reinforces Troops Guarding Rail Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Additional government troops are
being dispatched today to the northwestern province of Battambang
to protect a major rail line linking the capital city and
Battambang, a local newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
The Rasmei Kampuchea daily reported that royal soldiers from
the fifth military district will help local militiamen protect the
line running from the Pursat border northwest through Mong Russei
district.
</P>
<P>
Khmer Rouge guerrillas regularly use dynamite, landmines, and
home-made explosives to cut the major transport line, it said.
</P>
<P>
A project which began on May 20 to rehabilitate the line has
been slowed down because of lack of construction materials, said
an official in charge of the work. 
