<HEADLINE> Home-made Bomb Causes Minor Damage in Paris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paris, June 3 (Xinhua) -- A home-made bomb, termed by the
police as a "very crude" device, exploded under a car in Paris'
Left Bank area today, causing minor damage but no casualties.
</P>
<P>
Police said anti-terrorist experts are investigating the
incident, but there was no immediate indication it was connected
to a wave of bomb attacks that rocked France last summer.
</P>
<P>
The previous bomb attacks were blamed on Algerian Islamic
militants.
</P>
<P>
Police said the latest bomb was manufactured from a pressure
cooker packed with an undisclosed substance and placed under a
vehicle in Linne Street in Paris' 5th district.
</P>
<P>
It exploded before dawn, destroying the car and shattering the
windows of nearby buildings. The owner of the vehicle, a woman
whom the police did not identify, has been questioned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
