<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading Japanese newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Asahi Yomiuri:
</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto said Monday he will send a
letter of apology to "comfort women" forced to provide sex services
for Japanese soldiers before and during World War II.
</P>
<P>
Yomiuri, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- The Federation of Banks Associations of Japan is likely to
agree to share a greater burden of the government's plan to
liquidate the seven failed "Jusen" housing loan firms.
</P>
<P>
Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- Finance and farm ministers will inform financial
institutions of their additional burden for the government's
"Jusen" liquidation plan. 
