<HEADLINE> OAS Opens 26th General Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The 26th General Assembly of
the Organization of American States (OAS) opened here today with a
call for the eradication of poverty and promotion of free trade in
this part of the world.
</P>
<P>
Economic and trade integration is one of the pillars on which
the new vision of the Americans is built, OAS Secretary General
Cesar Gaviria said in his speech.
</P>
<P>
"We need to exert our efforts to work for a great undertaking
that will bring us closer to being an America united by a common
effort," the former Colombian president added.
</P>
<P>
Trade among regional blocs has intensified, said Gaviria,
citing the trade between the United States and Latin America and
the Caribbean, which has increased 72 percent since 1990.
</P>
<P>
Canada, for its part, increased its exports to Latin America
and the Caribbean by 30 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of a clear course for hemispherical economic
integration has been approved by trade ministers of the region.
</P>
<P>
In order to attain the goal of building "a free trade zone by
2005, we need to understand integration as a political project
that is of concern to all."
</P>
<P>
The OAS general assembly, to be closed on June 7, was attended
by foreign ministers and other officials of the organization's 35
member countries.
</P>
<P>
The OAS is aimed at closer cooperation among its member states
in promoting the integration process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
