<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Exports to Germany Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Thai exports to Germany posted 2.1
billion U.S. dollars in value last year, down 4.1 percent compared
with the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to data from the German-Thai Chamber of Commerce, the
decline was attributed to a drop in Thailand's exports of
textiles, jewelry and food products.
</P>
<P>
However, Thai imports from the west European country rose to
3.6 billion dollars, up 19.5 percent from that of 1994.
</P>
<P>
The highest increase in imports was in machines and tools, up
45.9 percent. Imports of metals, bars, sheets, tubes and alloys
grew by 32 percent, while paper and board imports increased 26.7
percent and cosmetics 25.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Germany is Thailand's most important trading partner in Europe
and the fourth largest trading partner in the world. The chamber
expects Thailand's demand for German products and technological
know-how to continue to rise.  
</P>
</TEXT>
