<HEADLINE> Thai Rice Exports Up in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's rice exports rose to
520,000 tons in May, 70,000 tons more than the planned target.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the Commerce Ministry, increasing
demand boosted the exports last month, despite the impact of heavy
rain on crops.
</P>
<P>
The increase in May swelled the total exports of rice in the
first five months of this year to 2.4 million tons, 15.4 percent
above the target.
</P>
<P>
Exports in the five months earned 21.42 billion baht (857
million U.S. dollars), compared with 20.06 billion baht (802
million U.S. dollars) from the sales abroad of 2.8 million tons in
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the trend might continue although fiercer
competition was expected owing to increased supplies.  
</P>
