<HEADLINE> Air China Adds Freighter Service to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Air China announced here tonight
that it would introduce the second freighter service to New York
on Tuesdays beginning in June to cope with the growing cargo
business.
</P>
<P>
Addressing an inaugural party tonight, Hong Jingrong, the
airliner's North America General Manager, said "to meet the need
of our business growth, we have decided to add the second
freighter service to New York."
</P>
<P>
Air China started its first freighter service to the United
States on Sundays six years ago, and the operation has been very
brisk. It now takes some 40 percent of the imported cargo load
from North America.
</P>
<P>
Air China, with a fleet of 64 aircraft, is known for its safety
record over the past decades. It has been awarded the Medal of
Honor by International Civil Aviation Organization as well as the
title "National Safety Pace-setter" by Civil Aviation
Administration of China. 
</P>
