<HEADLINE> French Jobless Rate Down 0.5 Percent for April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The jobless rate in France stood at
11.9 percent in April, or down 0.5 percent from March, according
to latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The total number of French people out of work were 3,012,000 in
April, or 15,400 less than the previous month, the country's Labor
Ministry said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Of that figure, more than one million, or 34.3 percent, were
long-term unemployed, namely those who had lost their jobs for at
least 12 months.
</P>
<P>
The number of long-term unemployed fell by 10,500 in April
while job offers made through France's national employment agency
were down by 0.8 percent. 
</P>
