<DATE_TIME> 1996-06-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Mercosur Summit to Be Held in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The second economic summit of
the Southern Cone Common Market (Mercosur) and the World Economic
Forum (WEF) will be held on June 23-25 in Buenos Aires, Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Besides some 400 executives and experts, the presidents and
economic cabinet members of Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay and
Paraguay will attend the meeting, WEF officials said today.
</P>
<P>
The perspectives of capital flows towards the Mercosur will be
analyzed at the summit.
</P>
<P>
There will also be a discussion on what the Mercosur can learn
from the Asian tigers -- South Korea, Singapore, Hong Kong, and
Taiwan, as well as on privatization in the future.
</P>
<P>
Inter-American Development Bank President Enrique Iglesias will
examine the Mercosur's perspectives for external growth.
</P>
<P>
Fringe working meetings will also be held on the regional
development of the automobile and food industries, financial
services and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The Mercosur, founded in March 1991, groups Argentina, Brazil,
Paraguay and Uruguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
