<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Visits Lithuania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VILNIUS, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Lithuanian Prime Minister
Laurinas-Mindaugas Stankyavicius today met Chinese Deputy Premier
Li Lanqing for talks on improving bilateral relations and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Stankyavicius and Li signed an agreement on the prevention of
double taxation in an effort to boost trade between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese deputy premier proposed that China and Lithuania
should diversify their cooperation into the fields of investment,
production and technology, expand Sino-Lithuanian trade relations
to include other countries and develop their cooperation into a
lasting partnership.
</P>
<P>
Stankyavicius said that his country is willing to maintain a
close relationship with China and learn from the successes of
China's special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
He expressed satisfaction over the inter-city cooperation
between Lithuania's Klaipeda and China's Shanghai, which are to
cooperate in manufacturing buses, tractors and household
electrical appliances.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese deputy premier is on an official tour of central
Europe which took him to Poland last week. 
</P>
