<HEADLINE> Myanmar Opens Embassies in Brasilia, Pretoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 4 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar today opened embassies in
Brasilia, capital of Brazil, and Pretoria, capital of South Africa
respectively, according to today's press releases of the Myanmar
Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
With a view to enhancing the existing friendly relations and
promoting bilateral trade and cooperation between Myanmar and the
two countries, Myanmar opened the two embassies, the press
releases said.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar established diplomatic relations with Brazil in
September 1982 and South Africa in April 1995.
</P>
<P>
Both Brazil and South Africa are the first countries in South
America and Southern Africa where Myanmar opened its embassies.
