<HEADLINE> Bulgarian-Chinese Trade Promotion Group Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Bulgarian-Chinese Economic
Relations Promotion Association was launched here today to boost
the bilateral trade of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Georgi Bulakieu, chairman of the newly established group, said
the association is aimed at increasing contacts and understanding
between the countries' companies and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The association, a non-profit organization, will use its
membership fees and donations from businesses to promote economic
cooperation between the countries.
</P>
<P>
Bulakieu said the association was sponsored by the
Bulgarian-Chinese Friendship Union and the Bulgarian-Chinese
friendship group in the National Assembly (parliament).
</P>
<P>
The volume of Sino-Bulgarian trade stood at 52.12 million
U.S. dollars in 1995, following a sharp drop from the previous
year. 
</P>
