<HEADLINE> Gontchenkov Wins 16th Stage in Tour of Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 3 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Alexandre Gontchenkov made a
solo run in the last 10 kilometers en route to his victory in the
16th stage of the Tour of Italy on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian broke away from a Swiss pair of Heinz Imboden and
Felice Puttini, and completed the 180-kilometer stage with a
margin of 20 seconds from Aosta, Italy to Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Chasing behind was another threesome including overall leader
Russian Pavel Tonkov, and Spaniard Abraham Olano dashed ahead in a
photo finish with 3 minutes 9 seconds behind the Ukrainian.
</P>
<P>
This was the first victory for Gontchenkov since 1993, which
enabled him to move up five places to 27th in the overall
standings, with 12 minutes 14 seconds behind Tonkov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
