<HEADLINE> Protection Station to be Built at Source of Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xining, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The name of an animal protection
worker who was killed by poachers is to live on at the source of
China's famous Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the first nature protection station at the
river's source is underway in Kekexili.
</P>
<P>
The protection station is being named after Juesang Sonandajie,
an official at Zhiduo County, Qinghai Province. He was killed by
poachers in 1994 while fighting with them to protect the wildlife.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by the spirit of Juesang Sonandajie, south China's
Shenzhen launched the campaign of "Protect the Source of Yangtze
River and Love Nature" and plans to build five nature protection
stations by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The area of Kekexili is the largest no-man's land in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
