<HEADLINE> Mango Festival to open in Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 4 (Xinhua) -- The first Changjiang Mango Festival
is scheduled to open on June 8, in the county of Changjiang,
Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
Trade negotiations, recreational activities and sightseeing
will also be conducted during the festival.
</P>
<P>
Mango, known as the "king of fruits," has been grown in
Changjiang for 1,000 years. It is now planted across 6,700
hectares in Changjiang and sold to 20 major cities including
Beijing and Shanghai, as well as Hong Kong and Macao. 
</P>
