<HEADLINE> China's First Pipeline of Finished Oil Near Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 4 (Xinhua) -- China's first pipeline transporting
finished oil products has been completed and is expected to be
brought into use in August. The pipeline links Karamay, a large
oilfield in northwest China's Xinjiang with Urumqi, its capital
city.
</P>
<P>
The 291-kilometer pipeline cost 260 million yuan and when the
entire project is completed it will pump 1.3 million tons of
finished oil products annually. Annual pumping capacity is
expected to jump to 2.3 million tons by the time all the pumping
stations are built.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu Hejun, an official overseeing the construction
project from Xinjiang Petroleum Administration Bureau, the project
will generate more than 100 million yuan in economic returns each
year and greatly ease the pressure on road transportation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
